race.comment: $3 million yearling ERNAUX (3) was disappointing as favourite when resuming, tiring to miss the placings. Best run last prep was second-up when a close third at Canterbury. Can improve enough to give this a shake. ROSA INCANTA (1) raced back in the field and wide before closing well to finish fifth when resuming in a strong form race over 1200m at Rosehill a month ago. Kept fresh and will find this easier so she is right in contention. PINK PERSUASION (5) is a daughter of Written Tycoon on debut for Chris Waller. Must respect off those factors alone. BRITISH GEM (9) has been trialling well so is worth keeping safe.
